SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 938
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Robert Bliss Walker
Harris of Henderson.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Robert Bliss Walker Harris of Henderson; and
WHEREAS, Robert Harris was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Harris was born on October 17, 1937, in Finger to the late Robert Bliss
and Mary Opal Walker Harris; he graduated from Bethel Springs High School in 1957; and
WHEREAS, in April 1956, Robert Harris married his grade school sweetheart, Betty, and
they made their home in Selmer until moving to Henderson in 1976; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Harris studied criminal justice at the University of Tennessee at Martin
and was a career Tennessee Highway Patrolman in West Tennessee for over thirty years; and
WHEREAS, Robert Harris enjoyed being outdoors, especially gardening, golfing, fishing,
and hunting, and he loved his home on the Tennessee River; and
WHEREAS, he will be sadly mourned but fondly remembered by his three sons, Phillip
(Pamela) Harris, John (Melinda) Harris, and Jason (Jenny) Harris; younger brother, Billy Frank
(Shirley) Harris; eight grandchildren, Holly (Nathan) Holladay, Alyssa (Steven) Toroni, Joshua
(Emily) Harris, Will Harris, Rachel Harris, Hardin Harris, Powers Harris, and Neyland Harris; and
nine great-grandchildren, Beckham Toroni, Emerson Holladay, Grayson Holladay, Maximus
Toroni, Savannah Toroni, Andrew Toroni, Millie Holladay, Penelope Harris, and Daphne Harris;
and
SJR0938
015544
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mr. Harris leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in public
life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should remember the
bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Robert Bliss Walker Harris,
reflecting fondly upon his impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the
examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Harris.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
